Omniverse Dreams — Third-Party Open Source Software Notice
===========================================================

This project will download and install additional third-party open
source software projects. Review the license terms of these open
source projects before use.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scope of this notice
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Omniverse Dreams is distributed as source (Python, CUDA/C++ extension source,
and package manifests). NVIDIA does not redistribute any third-party binaries
in this repository. However, building and running Omniverse Dreams on your
machine triggers third-party downloads that are fetched directly onto your
host (not staged or re-hosted by NVIDIA):

  1. `uv sync` (and `pip install`) resolves Python runtime dependencies
     from `samples/interactive-drive/pyproject.toml`, fetching wheels from
     PyPI and NVIDIA-internal package indexes onto your environment.
     Headless / Dockerized batch inference is
     handled by the companion `flashdreams` project at
     https://github.com/NVIDIA/flashdreams (private at time of writing).

  2. First-run asset pulls from Hugging Face Hub stage model
     checkpoints, tokenizer weights, and sample clips onto your
     Hugging Face cache.

You are responsible for reviewing the license terms of the third-party
software fetched by these steps before use in your environment.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Canonical third-party attribution files for this release
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For Apache-2.0 §4(d) purposes, the canonical attribution files distributed
with this release are:

  * `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt` (repo root) — per-component attribution for
    third-party source vendored or adapted into this repository, plus the
    auto-generated direct-runtime-dependency appendix.

  * `post-training/THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md` — per-component attribution and
    full upstream license texts (MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD-3-Clause) for the
    vendored / adapted third-party source under the `post-training/`
    subtree, including HuggingFace `diffusers`, HuggingFace `transformers`,
    OpenAI CLIP, mlfoundations `open_clip`, Self-Forcing, nanoGPT, `fvcore`,
    `torchtitan`, Intel OIDN, IRASim, `diffusion_policy`, and RetinaFace.

  * `samples/interactive-drive/NOTICE` — provenance for the inlined
    `interactive-drive` sample subtree (scoped to that subtree only).

Per-file SPDX license metadata is recorded in `REUSE.toml` at the repo root
and in `post-training/REUSE.toml` for the post-training subtree.

This `NOTICE` file (above) is the runtime / download notice required by
Apache-2.0 §4(d) for the redistributed source; the files listed in this
section are the canonical third-party attribution files for the release.
